  "title": "[Long-term Part-time] Order Fulfillment Associate - $10/hr",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Role Overview</strong></h3><p>You will be responsible for packing products into boxes, preparing customer orders, and ensuring smooth day-to-day fulfillment processes. This role is ideal for someone who is organized, detail-oriented, hands-on, and comfortable working in a warehouse (air-conditioned) environment. Hours are flexible depending on order volume and promotion peaks.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Pick, pack, and prepare customer orders according to daily fulfillment lists</li><li>Assemble and pack products into boxes</li><li>Ensure orders are packed accurately and meet quality standards</li><li>Maintain cleanliness and organization of the warehouse workspace</li><li>Restock inventory and perform basic stock counts when needed</li><li>Use basic fulfillment software (training provided) to update order status</li><li>Assist with ad-hoc warehouse tasks as required</li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Able to work in a warehouse (air-conditioned) environment</li><li>Good attention to detail and ability to work efficiently</li><li>Basic computer literacy to understand order processing flows</li><li>Physically able to carry boxes and stand for extended periods</li><li>Responsible, punctual, and able to work independently</li><li>Flexible to work more hours during promotion or peak seasons</li></ul><h3><strong>Working Hours</strong></h3><ul><li>2-8 working hours per day </li><li>Monday to Friday</li></ul><p></p>",
